FT  24 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Clinton Cards rises to Pounds 3m
Clinton Cards, the specialist retailer, reported further progress in the
year to January 29 as profits continued their recovery from Pounds 2.31m to
Pounds 3.02m pre-tax. Turnover, ex VAT, was higher at Pounds 75.9m against
Pounds 68.2m.
There was a 15 per cent rise in operating profits to Pounds 3.46m (Pounds
3.01m). The pre-tax figure was further helped by lower net interest charges
of Pounds 439,000 (Pounds 701,000).
Earnings per share came out at 11.61p (9.76p) and a final dividend of 3.11p
is recommended for a total of 4.71p (4.25p).
